      "location": "getOrderHistory, SQL query"
    },
    {
      "title": "No total count returned — clients cannot render pagination controls",
      "description": "The function returns only `Order[]` with no total count or has-next-page indicator. Clients cannot know how many pages exist, whether the current page is the last, or render page numbers. A second `SELECT COUNT(*)` or a `LIMIT pageSize+1` trick would solve this.",
      "location": "getOrderHistory, return type"
    }
  ],

  "suggestions": [
    "OFFSET-based pagination degrades on deep pages (OFFSET 100000 still scans 100K rows). For large order histories, consider cursor-based pagination keyed on `created_at` + `id`.",
    "Add an index on `(customer_id, created_at DESC)` if one does not already exist — without it, every page request does a full table scan filtered by customer_id.",
    "Consider returning a typed response object `{ orders: Order[], totalCount: number, hasNextPage: boolean }` instead of a bare array."
